Description: Novations Inc. is a privately held innovation creation firm founded in 1998. It's principal and founder, Marc Blumenthal, has an extensive
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Novations Inc. is a privately held innovation creation firm founded in 1998. It's principal and founder, Marc Blumenthal, has an extensive background in investment management, entrepreneurship, education and technology innovation. At the age of 19, while a student at the University of Pennsylvania, he participated in his first startup company as Vice President of The American Book Club, a pre-internet predecessor to Amazon.com. After gaining a teaching certification, he began his second start-up, The Learning Guild, which developed a wide variety of innovative educational programs involving millions of students, teachers and adults throughout the Northeast. During this time, Mr. Blumenthal also provided marketing consulting services to a wide variety of clients including the US Department of Agriculture, Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT), State Street Bank and the American Management Association. Following his marketing consulting and education work, he formed Novations, Inc. and became Managing Director of a multi-million dollar limited investment partnership. Since leaving the partnership, Mr. Blumenthal has focused on a select few Venture Capital opportunities that demonstrate the potential to provide significant value added propositions to major markets in the fields of Medical Devices, Aerospace, Hospitality and Personal Care Products. In addition to these "commercial" ventures, Mr. Blumenthal has authored the design of several sustainable "social" ventures that apply a business approach to solving public sector problems.  Venture underwriting will be sought for each of these "novations" as they mature and develop over the next several years.

Description: Contextual geotagging developer platform
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Geolenz provides an easy to use, smart platform for developing very robust, contextual geocoding applications for large brands and the independent developer community.   Location Aware Technologies The "location aware" technology world is emerging with a new breed of unique and useful applications and new ideas made possible by geotagging. Right now, however, there is still a rather wide gap between the promise of quality location based services (LBS) and the practical, productive use of location aware applications.  Geolenz's Smart Geocoding helps our customers and partners with rapid time to market deployment.    Geolenz was conceived to bridge this gap. Not a year from now or five years from now, but today. Our patent pending technology is the first-of-its-kind resource for enabling developers and businesses to rapidly deliver precise contextual data for geospatial locations associated with their applications. It doesn't matter whether the client applications are using photos, tweets, texts or other media assets with coordinates, it's all good. Our service consumes those coordinates and then rapidly enhances them with rich, contextual information derived from our unique recognition of geospatial relationships in given environments.

Description: Pistilli Realty Group is located in Astoria, New York.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: "The lease is signed and you have finally found the right place. It’s every New Yorker’s assumption and nightmare that all the good luck will soon come to an end and the reign of an awful building or land lord is soon to follow. Unfortunately, this dreaded nightmare happens more times than you would think. When something in your building doesn’t go as planned you need a management team you can trust. At Pistilli Realty, those nightmares do not become a reality. Our skilled and certified team, effectively reconstructs, revamps and maintains each of our buildings so that they are livable and enjoyable for both residents and business owners. Each building we purchase is full of character, charm and most importantly certified by New York State residential codes. We take pride in our properties and believe that the proper building can make all the difference when renting or selling a piece of property. Along with maintaining a sound building structure it is in our best interest to make you feel most at home. Whether it be an office for a large company or a residency of 3, we want your New York space to feel like your home in the Big Apple. As mentioned before, each of our buildings has been inspected, surveyed and approved through New York City laws. Our goal is not to rent it and forget it, we want to see our customers coming back for more and enjoying where they spend their time. We do our best to be environmentally friendly and to preserve the history that comes along with many of our buildings. Preserving the aesthetic appeal of classic New York architecture while, giving the building a modern twist is one of our specialties. We’ve taken famous industrial spaces like Pistilli Riverview East and Pistilli Tower and have turned them into functional modern offices and apartments. Restoring these old industrial buildings helps to reduce environmental harm and allows our residents to enjoy the classic architectural charm of the Big Apple. Even though structure is a technical term to take into consideration, it is a very important. Your environment is everything! It’s important for you to feel safe and a comfortable in New York. Come to us, we’ll find you a safe, attractive and accessible space that you will enjoy coming back to every day!"

Because this chronic condition is directly related to your work schedule, it may continue as long as work hours interfere with the body’s natural wake-sleep cycle.
